        <!-- Tab Content -->
        
        <!-- Introduction Tab -->
        <div id="tab-intro" class="tab-content active">
            <h2>Welcome to Session 3!</h2>
            
            <div class="info-box">
                <strong>Today's Focus:</strong> Word-building — mastering noun, verb, and adjective forms of environmental vocabulary. We'll practice using these forms accurately across all four skills.
            </div>

            <div class="activity-card">
                <h3>Learning Goals</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Language focus:</strong> Word-building — noun, verb, and adjective forms of environmental vocabulary</li>
                    <li><strong>Skill 1 — Reading:</strong> Comprehension, inference, and identifying word forms in context</li>
                    <li><strong>Skill 2 — Speaking:</strong> Extended turn, presenting an argument using varied vocabulary</li>
                    <li><strong>Skill 3 — Writing:</strong> Discursive paragraph with accurate use of word families</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="note">
                <strong>Why word-building?</strong> Sessions 1 and 2 covered grammar points. Session 3 keeps the language load light — one vocabulary focus — so you can direct most of your cognitive energy toward the four skills themselves.
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
                <h3>🌟 21st Century Skills in This Session</h3>
                <div style="margin-top: 1rem;">
                    <span class="skill-badge">Social Responsibility</span>
                    <span class="skill-badge">Critical Thinking</span>
                    <span class="skill-badge">Creative Thinking</span>
                    <span class="skill-badge">Learning to Learn</span>
                    <span class="skill-badge">Collaborative Working</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Presentation Tab -->
        <div id="tab-presentation" class="tab-content">
            <h2>📚 Presentation: Word-Building Families</h2>
            
            <h3>Key Word Families</h3>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Root</th>
                        <th>Noun</th>
                        <th>Verb</th>
                        <th>Adjective</th>
                        <th>Adverb</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>pollute</strong></td>
                        <td>pollution, pollutant</td>
                        <td>pollute</td>
                        <td>polluted, polluting</td>
                        <td>—</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>sustain</strong></td>
                        <td>sustainability</td>
                        <td>sustain</td>
                        <td>sustainable</td>
                        <td>sustainably</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>destroy</strong></td>
                        <td>destruction</td>
                        <td>destroy</td>
                        <td>destructive</td>
                        <td>destructively</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>conserve</strong></td>
                        <td>conservation</td>
                        <td>conserve</td>
                        <td>conservative</td>
                        <td>conservatively</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>erode</strong></td>
                        <td>erosion</td>
                        <td>erode</td>
                        <td>erosive, eroded</td>
                        <td>—</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>environment</strong></td>
                        <td>environment</td>
                        <td>—</td>
                        <td>environmental</td>
                        <td>environmentally</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>globe</strong></td>
                        <td>globe, globalisation</td>
                        <td>globalise</td>
                        <td>global</td>
                        <td>globally</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <div class="note">
                <strong>Key Teaching Points:</strong>
                <ul style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">
                    <li>Noun suffixes: <em>-tion, -ity, -ment, -ist, -ance</em></li>
                    <li>Adjective suffixes: <em>-al, -ive, -able, -ed, -ing</em></li>
                    <li>Adverb suffix: <em>-ly</em> (added to adjectives)</li>
                    <li>Verbs are usually the base form without special suffixes</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="activity-card" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
                <h3>Concept Check Questions</h3>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Think about these questions as you study the word families:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>If I say 'the environment is in danger', what part of speech is 'environment'?</li>
                    <li>How would you turn 'destroy' into a noun? What suffix do you add?</li>
                    <li>Can you make a sentence where 'sustainable' and 'sustainably' both appear correctly?</li>
                    <li>What is the difference between 'polluted' and 'polluting'?</li>
                    <li>Is 'environmental' a noun or an adjective? How do you know?</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Warmer 1 Tab -->
        <div id="tab-warmer1" class="tab-content">
            <h2>🔥 Warmer: "What's the word?"</h2>
            
            <div class="activity-card">
                <h3><span class="activity-number">1</span>Vocabulary Family Activation</h3>
                <p>For each word given, write as many related forms as you can (noun, verb, adjective, adverb). You have 30 seconds per word!</p>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                    <h4>Word: <em>pollute</em></h4>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Write all related forms you can think of...">
                    
                    <h4>Word: <em>destroy</em></h4>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Write all related forms you can think of...">
                    
                    <h4>Word: <em>sustain</em></h4>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Write all related forms you can think of...">
                    
                    <h4>Word: <em>erode</em></h4>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Write all related forms you can think of...">
                    
                    <h4>Word: <em>conserve</em></h4>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Write all related forms you can think of...">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="note">
                <strong>Learning to Learn:</strong> Which word family was easiest? Why? What strategy did you use — did you build from the root word, or did you try to remember words you've seen?
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Warmer 2 Tab -->
        <div id="tab-warmer2" class="tab-content">
            <h2>🎯 Warmer: "Odd One Out"</h2>
            
            <div class="activity-card">
                <h3><span class="activity-number">2</span>Find and Correct the Errors</h3>
                <p>Three sentences below. Two use correct word forms; one has an error. Identify which sentence is wrong and correct it.</p>
                
                <div class="sentence-box">
                    <strong>a)</strong> "The destruction of rainforests is one of the most pressing environment issues."
                </div>
                
                <div class="sentence-box">
                    <strong>b)</strong> "We need to act sustainably if we want to protect future generations."
                </div>
                
                <div class="sentence-box">
                    <strong>c)</strong> "Erosive of coastal areas is getting worse every year."
                </div>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                    <label style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy);">Which sentence has an error?</label>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Write the letter (a, b, or c)">
                    
                    <label style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); margin-top: 1rem; display: block;">Write the corrected version:</label>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Write the sentence correctly...">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="note">
                <strong>Hint:</strong> Look carefully at whether each word is being used as a noun, verb, adjective, or adverb. Does the sentence structure require that particular form?
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Practice Tab -->
        <div id="tab-practice" class="tab-content">
            <h2>✏️ Controlled Practice: Family Tree Gap-Fill</h2>
            
            <div class="activity-card">
                <h3><span class="activity-number">3</span>Complete the Word Families</h3>
                <p>Fill in the missing forms. Then use any three words from the table in original sentences about the environment.</p>
                
                <table class="gap-fill-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Noun</th>
                            <th>Verb</th>
                            <th>Adjective</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td>pollution</td>
                            <td><input type="text" placeholder="?"></td>
                            <td><input type="text" placeholder="?"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><input type="text" placeholder="?"></td>
                            <td>sustain</td>
                            <td>sustainable</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>destruction</td>
                            <td><input type="text" placeholder="?"></td>
                            <td>destructive</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><input type="text" placeholder="?"></td>
                            <td>conserve</td>
                            <td><input type="text" placeholder="?"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>erosion</td>
                            <td>erode</td>
                            <td><input type="text" placeholder="?"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><input type="text" placeholder="?"></td>
                            <td>globalise</td>
                            <td><input type="text" placeholder="?"></td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                    <h4>Write three original sentences using words from the table:</h4>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Sentence 1...">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Sentence 2...">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Sentence 3...">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="note">
                <strong>Collaborative Working:</strong> Work together with your teacher on this activity — take turns filling in rows and checking each other's work.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Reading Tab -->
        <div id="tab-reading" class="tab-content">
            <h2>📖 Reading: Word-Form Hunting</h2>
            
            <div class="activity-card">
                <h3><span class="activity-number">4</span>Scan the Unit 8 Main Text</h3>
                <p>After reading the text together, complete this word-form hunting task:</p>
                
                <div class="note">
                    Find and write down:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Two examples of a <strong>noun</strong> form of an environmental word</li>
                        <li>Two examples of an <strong>adjective</strong> form</li>
                        <li>One example of an <strong>adverb</strong></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                    <label style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--teal-dark);">Noun examples:</label>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Example 1">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Example 2">
                    
                    <label style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--teal-dark); margin-top: 1rem; display: block;">Adjective examples:</label>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Example 1">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Example 2">
                    
                    <label style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--teal-dark); margin-top: 1rem; display: block;">Adverb example:</label>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Example">
                </div>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
                    <h4>Inference Question (Critical Thinking):</h4>
                    <p>Is the writer's tone mostly optimistic or pessimistic? Find two words or phrases that support your answer.</p>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Tone: optimistic or pessimistic?">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Supporting evidence 1">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Supporting evidence 2">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="note">
                <strong>Social Responsibility:</strong> Does anything in this text describe a situation you've actually seen or experienced in Indonesia?
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Speaking Tab -->
        <div id="tab-speaking" class="tab-content">
            <h2>🗣️ Production: Extended Speaking</h2>
            
            <div class="activity-card">
                <h3><span class="activity-number">5</span>2-Minute Presentation</h3>
                
                <div class="prompt-box">
                    <strong>Choose ONE prompt:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 0.8rem; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
                        <li>"What is the single most destructive human habit affecting the environment? What would you recommend?"</li>
